<HEADLINE>
<P>
RONALD E. ETHERIDGE; LED SANTA BARBARA SCHOOLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ronald E. Etheridge, superintendent of schools for Santa Barbara until illness 
forced him to resign last year, died of leiomyo sarcoma Jan. 23 after battling 
that rare form of cancer for three years.He was 51 and died in Santa Barbara. 
</P>
<P>
 Etheridge came to Southern California in 1991 from Columbus, Ohio, where he 
had been school superintendent. 
</P>
<P>
 Earlier in Virginia, his native state, he had been an educator and 
administrator. 
</P>
