<HEADLINE>
<P>
WRESTLING ROUNDUP; IRVINE WILL COMPETE AT SECTION MEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Irvine won the right to represent the Sea View League in the Southern Section 
dual-meet championships by beating Santa Margarita, 64-0, Thursday at Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine, ranked fifth in Orange County, and University were tied with 5-0-1 
records.The teams had tied in a dual match, so the championship came down to 
team points. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine started the night five points ahead of University, but left no doubt 
with the 64-point victory. University beat Corona del Mar, 38-18, also 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine had five pins in the match, including one in 27 seconds by Steve Ruiz 
at 160 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
 "There was definite pressure on both sides to do well," Irvine Coach John 
Phillips said. 
</P>
<P>
 In Empire League wrestling: 
</P>
<P>
 El Dorado 43, Loara 23 -- El Dorado (12-0, 4-0), ranked sixth in Orange 
County, clinched at least a tie for the Empire League title with the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 The Golden Hawks got off to a quick start when brothers Rod and Rich Harvey 
won the first two matches. Rod Harvey (103 pounds) won a 13-4 decision over 
Anthony Pham and Rich Harvey (112) pinned Marty Fellbaum.  
</P>
<P>
 Damon Baughn (135 pounds), recovering from the flu, pinned his opponent in 
1:01. Toby Williams (189) won a 14-9 decision to help seal the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 El Dorado's final match is Tuesday against Katella. Loara is 2-2 in league. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Alamitos 43, Katella 22 -- Behind in points, Parker Mitchell of Los 
Alamitos pinned Bruno Martinez with one second remaining in the 125-pound 
match. Senior Clay Kemp (160 pounds) pinned Adam Calvert of Katella in 37 
seconds. Los Alamitos (5-1, 3-1) is second in the league. 
</P>
<P>
 The Griffins' only loss was to first-place El Dorado. 
</P>
<P>
 If the Griffins beat Esperanza Tuesday, it will be their first trip to the 
Southern Section tournament. Katella is 20-7-2, 1-3. 
</P>
