<TEXT>
<P>
 The Sea View League boys' soccer game between Newport Harbor and Woodbridge 
was stopped 17 minutes into the second half because of a fight involving 
players from both teams. The officials left the field after the teams were 
separated. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor led, 3-2, at the time. Newport Harbor trailed, 2-1, at the half 
but rallied for two goals early in the second half before the altercation 
started. 
</P>
<P>
 The outcome of the game hasn't been determined. 
</P>
<P>
 In another Sea View League boys' soccer game: 
</P>
