<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; VILLAGE CHRISTIAN GIRLS WIN 20TH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 On a night when Village Christian High's girls' basketball team won its 20th 
game, Clanci Lehman and Laura Wagenveld had career-high scoring games. 
</P>
<P>
 The Crusaders routed Maranatha, 78-35, and improved to 20-1, 7-0 in Alpha 
League play. Lehman had 20 points and 10 rebounds; Wagenveld had 16 points and 
11 rebounds. Trisha Palmquist added 16 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Alemany 78, Louisville 35 -- The Indians also picked up their 20th victory and 
remained undefeated. Carly Funicello led all scorers with 20 points as Alemany 
moved to 20-0, 9-0 in Mission League play. The Indians had every player on 
their roster score. 
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys 51, Monroe 42 -- Tami Matsuguma scored 15 points for the visiting 
Wolves in a Valley Pac-8 game. Monroe Center Dimara Haymond grabbed 15 rebounds 
and scored eight points. 
</P>
<P>
 Notre Dame 48, Harvard-Westlake 33 -- Valery Brady led all scorers with 17 
points while Maggie Dixon added 10 points and grabbed 18 rebounds to lead the 
visiting Knights (12-8, 5-4) in the Mission League game. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory qualified Notre Dame for the CIF Southern Section playoffs for the 
first time in four years, as well as tying the school record for wins in a 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 L.A. Baptist 55, Canyon 26 -- Senior forward Lori Neville scored 24 points to 
lead the Knights, who allowed just 11 points through the first three periods. 
Darcie Frazer added 12 points and eight steals for L.A. Baptist. 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley 43, Royal 32 -- Sarah Griffin scored 12 points and teammate Kim 
Butler added 10 for the Pioneers in a Marmonte league game. Royal's Tawnee 
Cooper was 10 of 14 from the free-throw line. 
</P>
<P>
 Bell-Jeff 66, St. Mary's 58 -- Forward Cathy Flores was dominant, scoring 23 
points to go along with 10 rebounds and seven assists as the Guards (18-4, 
10-1) won in a Camino Real League game. 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park 62 Thousand Oaks 43 -- Kara McKeowen scored 18 points and grabbed 
14 rebounds to lead the Panthers to their first victory over Thousand Oaks in 
nine years. BOYS' BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon 84, L.A. Baptist 60 -- Greg Minor's 31-point performance led the host 
Cowboys (17-5) in a nonleague romp, while Charles Woodard added 15 points and 
grabbed 10 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 The Knights (14-6) actually held a seven-point lead with 5:38 remaining in the 
second quarter before the Canyon press took effect, allowing the Cowboys to go 
on a 19-3 run. 
</P>
<P>
 Buckley 54, Yula 47 -- T.J. Jackson scored 26 points and had eight steals for 
the host Griffins (10-7, 7-3) in a Liberty League game. 
</P>
<P>
 Eagle Rock 41, Verdugo Hills 34-Yammar Carbonell scored 15 points for the host 
Eagles in the Northern Conference game. BOYS' SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
 Oak Park 4, Carpinteria 0 -- Chris Gorlitz and Chris Bramer each scored a pair 
of goals as the visiting Eagles improved to 9-1 in Tri-Valley league play and 
12-4 overall. 
</P>
<P>
 Agoura 3, Westlake 1 (OT) -- Mike Sanders scored twice to lead the visiting 
Chargers (5-10-3, 3-7-2) to the Marmonte League overtime victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Sanders' first goal came at the 60-minute mark in regulation play, tying the 
score at 1-1. After Harrison Choi scored the go-ahead goal in the 94th minute, 
Sanders found the net again three minutes later to ice the game for Agoura. 
</P>
<P>
 Casey Barber had the lone goal for the Warriors. 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks 2, Newbury Park 2 -- Tyler Rice scored to put visiting Thousand 
Oaks (10-6-1, 7-4-1) ahead in the first overtime, but with five minutes 
remaining in the second overtime, Alan Milin retied the score. 
</P>
