<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; CAREGIVERS TO HONOR 2 COUNTY SENIORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Ventura County senior citizens who have dedicated much of their lives to 
serving others will be honored by a senior care group at a special dinner next 
week. 
</P>
<P>
 Myra Harrison, president of Harrison Industries, and Lloyd Fellows, an 
ordained minister and clinical psychologist, will be presented with 
Distinguished Senior awards from Caregivers Inc., a Ventura-based nonprofit 
organization that provides help to needy seniors. 
</P>
<P>
 Myra Harrison, who lives in Ventura, is the widow of E. J. Harrison, who 
founded the local trash collection firm that bears his name. 
</P>
<P>
 "She has been very much involved in the community, and done a lot of volunteer 
service," said Pat Meredith, a spokeswoman for Caregivers. "Then, when (the 
Harrisons) became successful, they began to give back in gratitude to Ventura 
County for being good to them." 
</P>
<P>
 Fellows, an Ojai resident, is now serving as foreman of the Ventura County 
Grand Jury. 
</P>
<P>
 He also is a qualified mental health worker who has served on the Caregivers 
advisory board and has worked extensively with the American Red Cross and its 
National Disaster Team. 
</P>
<P>
 The Feb. 13 dinner also will honor actor Macdonald Carey, who is best known 
for his 25-year role on "Days of Our Lives." Carey will receive a special 
tribute for his work in the mental health community. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets for the dinner, which will be held at the Mandalay Beach Resort in 
Oxnard, cost $100. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
