<P>
PLANNERS TO CONSIDER OUTLET MALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Camarillo Planning Commission today will consider approving a 22-acre 
factory outlet mall west of the Ventura Freeway, between Las Posas Road and 
Carmen Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 The commissioners will consider the controversial Koll Leonard factory outlet 
mall for the second time after a Ventura Superior Court judge decided that a 
previous development deal amounted to a gift of public funds by the city.The 
decision was sparked by a lawsuit brought by an Oxnard developer and a retired 
Camarillo businessman. 
</P>
<P>
 Before approving the 250,000-square-foot mall, the commissioners must first 
certify the project's new environmental impact report, as required by the 
lawsuit. 
</P>
<P>
 If approved, the mall will be the second in Ventura County. A similar-sized 
facility recently broke ground in Oxnard about five miles north of the proposed 
Camarillo mall. 
</P>
<P>
 The commission meeting will start at 4 p.m. at City Hall, 601 Carmen Drive. 
J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
