<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; WOMAN KILLED IN ACCIDENT; INFANT INJURED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A young Lancaster woman was killed and a 4-month old infant injured Thursday 
when the woman's car slammed into the back of semi-trailer truck that slowed to 
make a right turn into a construction site, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Michelle Snyder, 21, was traveling north on Sierra Highway near Avenue O in 
Palmdale when the accident occurred about 9 a.m., Los Angeles County Sheriff's 
Deputy Gil Arce said. 
</P>
<P>
 Snyder died a short time later at Antelope Valley Hospital Medical Center, 
where the infant, who was not her child, was listed in good condition, Arce 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The truck driver was not cited, Arce said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
