<HEADLINE>
<P>
VELASQUEZ INJURED, WILL BE OUT 2 MONTHS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jorge Velasquez, a Hall of Fame jockey, fractured his pelvis Thursday when a 
horse he was working out collapsed and pinned him down at Calder Race Course. 
</P>
<P>
 Velasquez, 47, is expected to be sidelined for two months, said Manuel 
Marrero, his agent. Velasquez was scheduled to ride Migrating Moon in 
Saturday's $300,000 Donn Handicap at Gulfstream Park. He was in the top 10 at 
the current Gulfstream meeting with nine winners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
