<TEXT>
<P>
 30-Year Mortgages Steady at 6.97%: The fixed-rate mortgages were unchanged 
from last week, according to a national survey released by the Federal Home 
Loan Mortgage Corp. The rates remained the lowest since Oct. 26, when they 
averaged 6.86%.After dropping to a 25-year low of 6.74% in October, rates rose 
to 7.31% in November, then began drifting lower. On one-year, adjustable rate 
mortgages, lenders were asking an average initial rate of 4.12%, down from 
4.16% last week. Fifteen-year mortgages, an increasingly popular option for 
people refinancing mortgages, averaged 6.46% this week, down from 6.47% a week 
earlier. The rates do not include add-on fees that are known as points. 
