</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Clinton Reportedly Drafting Plan for Free-Trade Zone: The Administration is 
drafting a plan that would create a Western Hemisphere free-trade zone in 10 to 
15 years and add Chile to the North American Free Trade Agreement by late next 
year, White House officials told the New York Times. While details remain 
unresolved, the plan could dominate the hemisphere's economic and political 
agendas in the next decade, the officials told the newspaper. 
</P>
