BRIEFLY: AEROSPACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Made-in-Japan Rocket Blasts Off: The first major rocket developed completely 
in Japan roared into space from a launch pad in Tanegashima.The country hopes 
the advanced H-II will lift Japan into the commercial satellite business. 
However, analysts say the cost of the H-II's leading-edge technology -- coupled 
with the strong yen -- will make it too expensive to compete in the tough 
satellite-launching market. The H-II was developed at a cost of $2.4 billion. 
</P>
