<P>
 Continental Reports 4th-Quarter Loss: The airline's losses nearly doubled at 
the end of last year, but the company said its results should gradually improve 
as it implements a new lower-fare service. Houston-based Continental lost $26.5 
million on revenue of $1.37 billion. A year earlier, it lost $13.9 million. 
