</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES BATES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Television: Home shopping channel ValueVision International launched a hostile 
bid for infomercial giant National Media Corp., offering $61.2 million, or 
$10.50 a share, for enough stock to seize control.The bid values National Media 
at $146 million. ValueVision, which already owns 1.2 million National Media 
shares, promised to offer the equivalent of $10.50 a share for the remaining 
shares if it succeeds in gaining a 50.2% stake. National Media has grown 
through infomercials such as "Juice Tiger," "Amazing Discoveries" and a pain 
relief infomercial staring Frankie Avalon. National Media's directors spurned a 
previous ValueVision offer. ValueVision has retained Salomon Bros. to help with 
financing. National Media declined to comment. JAMES BATES 
