<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: SAN FERNANDO VALLEY; 4 
UNLICENSED CONTRACTORS ARRESTED IN SPOT CHECK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police separately arrested four unlicensed contractors in the San Fernando 
Valley on Thursday in the department's first post-quake crackdown on illegal 
construction activity. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said Daniel Gonzales, 37, of Reseda; Juan Ortiz, 35, of South Gate; 
Agustine Serrano, 33, of Canoga Park, and Jose Flores, 27, of Sylmar were each 
charged with one felony count of contracting without a license in a declared 
disaster area.If convicted, the men face a maximum sentence of up to 16 months 
in prison and a fine of up to $10,000. 
</P>
<P>
 The men were arrested during a spot check of residential construction activity 
in Granada Hills and Porter Ranch. Lt. Ken Welty of the LAPD's fraud unit said 
more random licensing checks are planned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA020494-0185 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 010393 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
February 4, 1994, Friday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
