<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES COUNTY; 
ADULT MAGAZINES BANNED FROM FIREHOUSE -- FOR NOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A federal judge refused Thursday to loosen a ban on adult magazines in county 
fire stations, but he told attorneys to prepare their arguments and come back 
March 10. 
</P>
<P>
 Fire Capt. Steven Johnson had sought a preliminary injunction against 
enforcement of the ban on Playboy, Penthouse and Playgirl, pending trial of his 
lawsuit.Johnson claims he has a 1st Amendment right to read the magazines. 
</P>
<P>
 The department, supported by the local chapter of the National Organization 
for Women, says the magazines violate sexual harassment policy. 
</P>
<P>
 U.S. District Judge Stephen Wilson said it was an unusual 1st Amendment case 
because Johnson works for the government. To get a preliminary injunction, 
Johnson would have to prove the county's policy was too general, covering any 
magazines that publish nude photos, the judge said. 
</P>
<P>
 Wilson indicated that the case would probably focus on whether Johnson's 
possession of a magazine would interfere with efficient operations, and whether 
the public would encounter the magazines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
