METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES COUNTY; 
1-MONTH BUS PASSES OFFERED TO QUAKE VICTIMS IN SHELTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Free one-month bus passes are available for Los Angeles County residents who 
were forced from their homes by the Jan. 17 earthquake, officials said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The monthly passes are being distributed at emergency shelters operated by the 
Red Cross and the Salvation Army in the San Fernando Valley and Hollywood 
areas. Passes will be available to anyone living in an emergency shelter who is 
receiving some type of federal assistance, Los Angeles County Metropolitan 
Transportation Authority officials said. 
</P>
