</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A cabdriver was shot to death in an apparent robbery, police said Thursday.No 
one was arrested. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses heard one or two shots and saw a young man running from the area on 
Raymond Avenue where the cab crashed into a parked truck and caught fire late 
Wednesday, Detective Bob Lopez said. The driver's heart had stopped when 
firefighters pulled him from the car about 9:30 p.m., Fire Department spokesman 
Brian Humphrey said. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver was pronounced dead at California Medical Center. His identity was 
not immediately known, police said. 
</P>
