<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; EL CAMINO 
REAL, KENNEDY WILL REOPEN ON FEB. 15 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 School officials said they will reopen El Camino Real and Kennedy high schools 
Feb. 15 -- two weeks earlier than planned -- because the state has assured the 
Los Angeles Unified School District that portable classrooms will be in place. 
</P>
<P>
 Associate Supt.Dan Isaacs said he expects the two campuses to resume classes 
in portable bungalows until earthquake-damaged classroom buildings are 
repaired. Parents who do not wish to wait may enroll their children in other 
high schools within the district for the semester, Isaacs said. 
</P>
<P>
 But he said the district expects about 95% of the students to return to El 
Camino Real and Kennedy when those campuses reopen. 
</P>
<P>
 Students and staff at Van Gogh Street Elementary in Granada Hills, which has 
been closed because of large cracks and fissures throughout the campus, will be 
relocated to Frost Middle School, officials said. Classes also will start Feb. 
15. 
</P>
</TEXT>
