ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: 4 BANKS PROVIDE WYLE LABS A $50-MILLION LINE OF CREDIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Wyle Laboratories went shopping for money to support last summer's major 
expansion efforts and walked away Thursday with a $50-million line of credit 
from four banks. 
</P>
<P>
 Wyle, one of the nation's larger marketers and distributors of high-technology 
electronic products, will use the money for working capital until 10 locations 
it opened last June in the Midwest and the East reach the break-even point, 
said Van Holland, the company's chief financial officer. 
</P>
<P>
 Wyle, which in September moved its corporate headquarters to Irvine from El 
Segundo, expects to reach that point this summer, Van Holland said. 
</P>
<P>
 The line of credit is being provided by Continental Bank in Chicago, Bank of 
New York, NationsBank in New York and NBD Bank in Detroit. 
