<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHILES SELECTED TO HEAD U.S. STRATEGIC COMMAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 President Clinton has nominated Vice Adm. Henry Chiles Jr. for appointment as 
commander-in-chief of the U.S. Strategic Command and promotion to admiral, the 
Pentagon announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 If confirmed by the Senate, Chiles, 56, would become the first admiral to head 
the new command, which brings all Air Force and Navy nuclear weapons under the 
command of a single unit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
