<HEADLINE>
<P>
DISNEY, CITY PLAN ICE RINK FOR YOUTH, MIGHTY DUCKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT LAIT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Walt Disney Co. and city officials said Thursday they are working on a 
joint venture to build an ice rink that would be used as a practice facility 
for the Mighty Ducks and a community youth center. 
</P>
<P>
 "Disney's proposal is very exciting," City Manager James D. Ruth said."Not 
only will it accommodate the Ducks, it will be used to attract, train and 
educate our young people about the game of hockey." 
</P>
<P>
 Ruth said plans for the rink are in the early stages, but he expects them to 
be formalized soon. He said under Disney's proposal, the city would provide the 
land and Disney would build the facility. 
</P>
<P>
 A specific site has not yet been chosen, and costs aren't known, but Ruth said 
it will probably be built in downtown Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
 Kenneth P. Wong, senior vice president of the Disney Development Co., 
confirmed that the company is looking into the venture with the city, but 
declined to elaborate on the details of the project. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's an idea that we've been discussing for some time," Wong said. "It will 
involve youth, the community and hockey." 
</P>
<P>
 Ruth said Disney is also thinking about creating a hockey program aimed at 
troubled youth to steer them away from gangs and drugs and into organized 
sports. 
</P>
<P>
 According to Ruth, the facility would probably be used more by the community 
than the Ducks. 
</P>
<P>
 "The Ducks will probably be in there only a couple hundred hours a year," he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ducks now practice at the Glacial Garden Ice Arena in Anaheim. MATT LAIT 
</P>
</TEXT>
