<HEADLINE>
<P>
TEEN RIDING IN ALLEY HAS BIKE, $200 STOLEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 15-year-old boy who was riding his bicycle in an alley Wednesday evening was 
robbed of $200 in cash by two youths who knocked him to the ground, then rode 
off on his bike, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim was riding in the 17300 block of Jacquelyn Lane about 7:20 p.m. 
when the robbery occurred, said Police Lt. Charles Poe. 
</P>
<P>
 "The two suspects, believed to be 12 and 16 years old, threatened the use of a 
gun, but no weapon was seen," Poe said. 
</P>
<P>
 The teen-ager was shaken but not injured in the attack. 
</P>
<P>
 Poe said investigators do not know why the victim was carrying so much cash, 
which the robbers took from his front shirt pocket. 
</P>
