<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Boulle obituary -- An obituary in Thursday's Times on Pierre Boulle, the 
French author of the best-selling novel "Bridge on the River Kwai," incorrectly 
stated that the screenplay for the film of the same title was written only by 
Carl Foreman using the name Michael Wilson. The screenplay was credited to the 
non-English-speaking Boulle as stated, but was actually written by both Foreman 
and Wilson, two blacklisted screenwriters who posthumously received the Academy 
Award for the script in 1985. Boulle died Sunday in Paris at the age of 81. 
</P>
